# Platform SEO Infrastructure — Do Not Break

## 1. All page metadata must be dynamic (all client apps)

Every `src/app/**/page.tsx` in any client app must use `generateMetadata` + `resolveTrackedPageMetadata`.
Never use `export const metadata: Metadata = {...}` on a page file — static exports bake metadata at build time, making admin-panel SEO edits invisible without a redeploy.

✅ Required pattern for all page files:
```tsx
import { resolveTrackedPageMetadata } from "@sweetmedia/admin-core";

const fallback: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title | Brand Name",
  description: "...",
  alternates: { canonical: "/route-path" },
};

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return resolveTrackedPageMetadata("/route-path", fallback);
}
```

❌ Never on a page file (layout.tsx root is the only exception):
```tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = { title: "...", description: "..." };
```

## 2. Every fallback must include `alternates.canonical`

`alternates: { canonical: "/exact-route-path" }` is required in every `fallback` metadata object on every page.

## 3. `/api/admin/revalidate` route must exist in every client app

This route calls `revalidatePath()` and is called by admin-core after applying SEO changes, making updates live instantly without a redeploy. Never delete it or remove the `revalidatePath()` call.

## 4. Blog slug pages are exempt from `resolveTrackedPageMetadata`

`/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` fetches metadata from the `blog_posts` table directly via `fetchPublishedBlogPostForMetadata`. This is correct — do not add `resolveTrackedPageMetadata` to these files.

## 5. Blog ISR settings must not change without explicit instruction

Blog index and blog slug routes use `export const revalidate = 3600` and `generateStaticParams`. Do not add `force-dynamic` or remove the `revalidate` export from these routes.

## 6. `robots.ts` must remain a dynamic route file

Each app's `src/app/robots.ts` generates the robots config dynamically. Do not replace it with a static `robots.txt`.

Brand `disallow` lists must use `mergeRobotsDisallow()` from `@sweetmedia/admin-core` so WordPress legacy paths (`/tag/`, `/category/`, `/feed/`, `/author/`, `/wp-admin/`, etc.) stay blocked on every client.

## 6b. `not-found.tsx` must export noindex metadata

Each app's `src/app/not-found.tsx` must export `metadata` using `NOT_FOUND_PAGE_METADATA` from `@sweetmedia/admin-core` so 404s (including dead WP URLs) send `noindex, nofollow`.

## 7. Root `layout.tsx` is the only place static metadata is allowed

`src/app/layout.tsx` uses `export const metadata` for the site-wide defaults (`metadataBase`, `title.template`). This is correct and must not be changed to `generateMetadata`.
